insight_cards.title: Market Performance
insight_cards.description: Google is presented as the most popular and accurate search engine with fast performance and broad feature coverage across Search, Images, Ads, Workspace, and AI integrations.

insight_cards.title: Competition Level
insight_cards.description: Multiple competitors and alternatives are actively referenced including Bing, DuckDuckGo, Startpage, Ecosia, Qwant and specialized image sources which maintain competitive pressure on privacy and niche features.

insight_cards.title: Privacy Sentiment
insight_cards.description: Search results repeatedly flag privacy concerns and recommend privacy-focused alternatives such as DuckDuckGo, Startpage and Brave Search while Google documents extensive privacy controls users can manage.

insight_cards.title: Monetization and Ad Pricing
insight_cards.description: Google Ads is highlighted as the primary monetization channel with typical CPC ranges cited and alternatives like Microsoft Advertising and Amazon Advertising noted for comparison.

insight_cards.title: AI Features Availability
insight_cards.description: Gemini and AI Mode in Search are referenced as new conversational features with limited regional availability and integration across Search, Chrome and Workspace reported.

recommended_actions.action: Simplify and highlight privacy controls and guidance pages to reduce perceived complexity and address recurring user privacy concerns referenced across search results.
recommended_actions.impact: Increase user trust and reduce churn to privacy-first alternatives

recommended_actions.action: Accelerate clear documentation and in-product prompts for AI Mode and Gemini features to address limited rollout confusion and support wider adoption.
recommended_actions.impact: Higher engagement with AI features and improved user experience

recommended_actions.action: Publish clearer small business guidance on expected CPC ranges and setup steps for Performance Max and Merchant Center workflows referenced in results.
recommended_actions.impact: Lower advertiser setup friction and improved ad spend efficiency

recommended_actions.action: Consolidate help center, recovery, and developer resources links into curated flows for common intents such as account recovery, device support, and developer onboarding.
recommended_actions.impact: Reduce support friction and improve self-service resolution rates

recommended_actions.action: Produce targeted content around common informational queries uncovered in the dataset such as image search filters, advanced search operators, account recovery, and Workspace comparisons.
recommended_actions.impact: Improve organic discovery for informational queries and reduce reliance on community sources
